<font color="#FF0000">THANK YOU NURSE..I MADE IT </font><br>
<tt>Thu May  8 23:07:42 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
As I came to from the morphine, laying on that table I felt the pain.<br>
People and voices all around me..sounded so far away..I felt so alone...<br>
so scared. I reached down and felt for the rest of me..and then I found out,<br>
it was gone. I screamed I think, and started to cry, funny, they always said<br>
Rangers don't cry. She walked into my blurred vision and took my hand and <br>
I remember the soft voice...the comforting touch..and that sweet smell...<br>
she hugged me and told me I was gonna be ok..I was alive.  For that one <br>
moment...she was my Mother, holding me and assuring me....I was ok.<br>
That woman was a Army Nurse...I don't even know her name...but if she's<br>
reading this..she know's who she is...Thanks, dosen't seem like enough,<br>
but all I can say is thanks, from a real scared 20 year old. I'll<br>
never forget you and the kindness you showed me that day..at the <br>
95th evac. God Bless all of the nurses
<p><code>-- STRSHP@aol.com  (Greg B) </code><p>


